snippet.textDisplay: The media is so stupid when it comes to defense and understanding the mentality of players trying to tell us how to think. Look, as a spectator I could clearly see what Beverly was saying... all he was saying is that without help from refs and calls, LeBron James isn't tough to shut down because he can have the defensive foot speed to contend with him and take away LeBron's game from the hip down because of the core-base of Beverly's defensive position merely based upon LBJ not posting up - which makes it easier for LBJ to be guarded by a solid defensive perimeter player.... Remember, no refs giving you calls and you'll see what will happen... LBJ's game is about ramming people over lowering the shoulder, getting the call and when the refs give him the whistle, it's not great offense, it's the refs: defensive players know this and fans know this but the media is trying to tell us what to think because of stats - LBJ doesn't play real basketball; most of his game is ref-given anyway.
